ort team and lead all support representatives at Apto, working collaboratively with our customers and internal stakeholders (business development, operations, compliance, and engineering). Responsibilities: Lead the Apto Tech Support and Customer Service (CS) team, train CS representatives and recruit new CS representatives as needs change. Create a world-class service culture that will continuously delight customers and cardholders. Create repeatable and scalable processes and procedures for customer service delivery of white-labeled programs managed by Apto. Oversee, train, and guide Apto's CS representatives. Exemplify customer success by serving as the voice of the cardholder and customer within Apto. Create, measure, and continuously improve Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) for customer service. Manage Apto's Knowledge Base and facilitate automation of CS activities to maximize efficiency. Requirements: 5+ years of providing hands-on customer service and technical support at a SaaS company. Experience in the Fintech industry is preferred. Experience in the card issuance industry with deep understanding of its ecosystem including cardholder enrollment and onboarding, bank issuance, transaction processing, and card fulfilment is a prefered. Passion for world-class customer service. Work experience in fast-paced start-up environments. Excellent written communication skills. Detail-oriented and well organized. A relevant academic degree that demonstrates quantitative and analytical orientation. Experience in working with Zendesk and Salesforce. Good understanding of card transaction processing, network settlements, dispute handling, and ISO 8583. Proven ability to read, debug, and understand API calls and to create and debug SQL queries. Ability to think critically and creatively about solving customer problems in both technical and business contexts. Strong sense of ownership and desire to deliver the best possible experience for customers. ayWhpEZeq0 Show full j